WEBVTT

00:02.468 --> 00:04.837
TONIGHT, GORDON HEADS
TO THE HAMPTONS

00:04.871 --> 00:06.906
FOR SOME TRADITIONAL
IRISH FARE.

00:06.939 --> 00:08.808
SPRING ROLLS WITH MUSTARD.

00:08.841 --> 00:11.044
BUT FINDS A FAMILY PUB
THAT'S LOST ITS WAY.

00:11.077 --> 00:12.278
GET OUTTA HERE.

00:12.311 --> 00:13.880
DOESN'T FEEL LIKE
A PUB AT ALL.

00:13.913 --> 00:14.847
THE FATHER'S STRUGGLING

00:14.881 --> 00:15.748
TO KEEP IT TOGETHER.

00:15.782 --> 00:16.983
WE'RE IN TROUBLE RIGHT NOW.

00:17.016 --> 00:18.885
GET OUTTA HERE.
GET OUTTA HERE.

00:18.918 --> 00:20.720
BUT THE SONS
ARE PULLING IT APART.

00:20.753 --> 00:22.655
YOU DON'T LISTEN
TO ANYTHING I WANT TO SAY.

00:22.689 --> 00:24.257
YOU ALMOST WANT TO TELL HIM
TO SHUT UP.

00:24.290 --> 00:26.159
ONE HIDES BEHIND THE BAR.

00:26.192 --> 00:27.627
I DO MY JOB.
EVERYBODY'S HAPPY AT THE BAR.

00:27.660 --> 00:29.195
EVERYTHING'S GOOD.

00:29.228 --> 00:30.000
THE OTHER
IS DRUNK WITH POWER.

00:30.000 --> 00:31.130
THE OTHER
IS DRUNK WITH POWER.

00:31.164 --> 00:33.199
ENOUGH.
GET OUTTA HERE.

00:33.232 --> 00:35.668
AND THE FOOD THEY SERVE...

00:35.702 --> 00:37.136
THIS IS LETHAL.

00:37.170 --> 00:38.805
HAS SENT
THE LOCALS PACKING.

00:38.838 --> 00:39.872
WE HAVE TO WORK

00:39.906 --> 00:41.674
AND REALLY DIG DEEP

00:41.708 --> 00:43.609
TO GET THESE LOCALS
BACK ON OUR SIDE.

00:43.643 --> 00:45.344
CHEF RAMSAY'S NOT
THE BEST COOK IN THE WORLD.

00:45.378 --> 00:47.046
HE THINKS HE KNOWS EVERYTHING
WHETHER HE DOES OR NOT.

00:47.080 --> 00:48.548
IF BRIAN WASN'T MY SON,
I'D HAVE FIRED HIM.

00:48.581 --> 00:50.049
YOU GOT AN ISSUE?

00:50.083 --> 00:51.884
I'M OUTTA HERE.

00:51.918 --> 00:54.087
WITH ONLY ONE WEEK
TO TURN IT AROUND...

00:54.120 --> 00:55.922
YOU CAN MOVE FASTER HERE,
LET'S GO.

00:55.955 --> 00:57.156
WILL GORDON BE ABLE TO FIND

00:57.190 --> 00:58.624
THIS FAMILY'S POT OF GOLD?

00:58.658 --> 01:00.000
EVERY DAY YOU HAVE TO
GIVE IT YOUR BEST SHOT.

01:00.000 --> 01:00.359
EVERY DAY YOU HAVE TO
GIVE IT YOUR BEST SHOT.

01:00.393 --> 01:04.063
OR HAS THE LUCK OF THE IRISH
RUN OUT?

01:04.097 --> 01:05.298
I DON'T SEE HOW
THIS IS GONNA WORK.

01:05.331 --> 01:06.699
WE'RE SCREWED.

01:06.733 --> 01:08.935
THAT'S COMING UP
ON KITCHEN NIGHTMARES.

01:29.055 --> 01:30.000
THE HAMPTONS
IS A BEAUTIFUL GETAWAY

01:30.000 --> 01:31.591
THE HAMPTONS
IS A BEAUTIFUL GETAWAY

01:31.624 --> 01:35.628
FOR THE RICH AND FAMOUS
IN THE SUMMER.

01:35.661 --> 01:37.797
BUT IN THE WINTER,
IT'S A QUAINT VILLAGE

01:37.830 --> 01:40.066
INHABITED BY
A TIGHT-KNIT COMMUNITY.

01:40.099 --> 01:43.169
AMONG THE MANY EATERIES HERE
IS FINN McCOOL'S,

01:43.202 --> 01:44.470
A FAMILY RESTAURANT

01:44.504 --> 01:48.641
WHICH IS UNFORTUNATELY DYING.

01:48.674 --> 01:51.878
GORDON RAMSAY IS HERE
TO BREATHE NEW LIFE INTO IT.

01:51.911 --> 01:53.613
I KNOW IT'S WINTER
BUT GOD,

01:53.646 --> 01:55.948
YOU'D THINK THERE'D
BE SOMEBODY AROUND HERE.

01:55.982 --> 01:59.619
THIS PLACE IS DESOLATE.
THERE'S HARDLY ANYBODY AROUND.

01:59.652 --> 02:00.000
AWW, COME ON.

02:00.000 --> 02:01.187
AWW, COME ON.

02:01.220 --> 02:04.290
YOU GOT A LOT
OF PREPPING TO DO.

02:04.323 --> 02:06.159
THERE HE GOES.

02:06.192 --> 02:07.794
I'M THE OWNER OF FINN McCOOL'S
FAMILY RESTAURANT

02:07.827 --> 02:09.095
AND IRISH PUB.

02:09.128 --> 02:12.932
* MY YOUNG LOVE
SAID TO ME *

02:12.965 --> 02:14.600
I WAS A POLICE OFFICER.

02:14.634 --> 02:16.369
I WORKED FOR THE SOUTHAMPTON
TOWN POLICE DEPARTMENT.

02:16.402 --> 02:18.171
I WAS THERE OVER 20 YEARS.

02:18.204 --> 02:19.539
ARE WE READY?

02:19.572 --> 02:20.940
THESE SHOULD BE MOVED
OVER HERE A LITTLE BIT.

02:20.973 --> 02:22.141
AND I RETIRED.

02:22.175 --> 02:24.443
AND I WAS RETIRED
FOR 12 HOURS,

02:24.477 --> 02:26.078
EIGHT OF WHICH I SLEPT,

02:26.112 --> 02:27.413
AND THEN WE OPENED UP.

02:27.446 --> 02:29.649
FINN McCOOL'S
FAMILY RESTAURANT

02:29.682 --> 02:30.000
WE ARE A FAMILY, I MEAN,
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE ALL ABOUT.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.684
WE ARE A FAMILY, I MEAN,
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE ALL ABOUT.

02:31.717 --> 02:33.719
SO THAT'S WHO
WE WANTED TO CATER TO.

02:33.753 --> 02:35.822
BOTH OF MY SONS
WORK HERE FULL TIME.

02:35.855 --> 02:38.191
AND JASON,
HE'S THE BAR MANAGER.

02:38.224 --> 02:40.159
WHAT'S UP?
CAN I GET
THOSE SHOTS?

02:40.193 --> 02:41.828
EVERYBODY'S HAPPY AT THE BAR.
EVERYTHING'S GOOD.

02:41.861 --> 02:43.362
YEAH, YEAH,
YEAH, YEAH.

02:43.396 --> 02:45.264
MY PROBLEMS
ARE MORE WITH MY BROTHER.

02:45.298 --> 02:47.033
I'M GONNA KICK YOU
RIGHT IN THE TEETH, I SWEAR--

02:47.066 --> 02:48.167
LET ME HELP YOU OUT.
GET OUTTA HERE.

02:48.201 --> 02:49.702
WHAT DO YOU
NEED ME TO DO?

02:49.735 --> 02:51.070
I WOULD DEFINITELY NOT RECOMMEND
WORKING WITH FAMILY.

02:51.103 --> 02:52.104
IT'S A PAIN IN THE ASS.

02:52.138 --> 02:53.139
YOU'RE AN ASS.

02:53.172 --> 02:54.874
I SWEAR TO  YOU ARE.

02:54.907 --> 02:56.509
I'M VERY GOOD
AT WHAT I DO.

02:56.542 --> 02:58.077
I DON'T KNOW
IF MY DAD AND MY BROTHER

02:58.110 --> 03:00.000
COULD SURVIVE WITHOUT ME
BEING IN THE KITCHEN.

03:00.000 --> 03:00.179
COULD SURVIVE WITHOUT ME
BEING IN THE KITCHEN.

03:00.213 --> 03:01.214
GO AWAY.

03:01.247 --> 03:02.548
AH, YOU GO AWAY.

03:02.582 --> 03:05.117
HE IS AN ARROGANT
LITTLE BASTARD.

03:06.519 --> 03:10.556
I DEVELOPED THE NAME
"CHEF SHORTCUT" FOR HIM

03:10.590 --> 03:12.191
BECAUSE HE JUST CUTS CORNERS.

03:12.225 --> 03:13.626
HE'LL DEEP-FRY BACON.

03:13.659 --> 03:15.328
AND THEY COME OUT
LIKE PIG'S TAILS.

03:15.361 --> 03:16.562
IT'S LIKE CHEWING
A BACON BALL.

03:16.596 --> 03:17.296
IT'S ABSURD.

03:17.330 --> 03:18.598
I'M IN CHARGE OF THE FOOD

03:18.631 --> 03:20.266
AND I HAVE MY NAME BEHIND IT.

03:20.299 --> 03:22.168
AND I KNOW WHAT CAN WORK
AND WHAT WILL WORK.

03:22.201 --> 03:23.636
HE CAN BE PRETTY COCKY
AT TIMES.

03:23.669 --> 03:25.304
YOU'RE SO
FULL OF CRAP.

03:25.338 --> 03:26.873
THERE ARE TIMES WHEN HE'S
VERY DISRESPECTFUL.

03:26.906 --> 03:28.140
ALL RIGHT,
LOOK AT ME.

03:28.174 --> 03:29.342
NO.
I SWEAR ON LILY.

03:29.375 --> 03:30.000
TO THE POINT WHERE I--

03:30.000 --> 03:30.776
TO THE POINT WHERE I--

03:30.810 --> 03:32.545
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THE THINGS THAT HE SAYS.

03:32.578 --> 03:33.813
WHAT DO YOU
NEED IT FOR?

03:33.846 --> 03:35.014
SO I CAN
THROW IT AT YOU.

03:35.047 --> 03:37.316
BRIAN AND JASON
BUTT HEADS A LOT.

03:37.350 --> 03:40.019
IT COMES PRETTY CLOSE
TO BLOWS.

03:41.487 --> 03:43.489
WELL, TELL HIM TO STAY
THE  OUT OF THE KITCHEN.

03:43.522 --> 03:45.091
JASON, YOU KNOW,
TRIES TO TALK TO HIM.

03:45.124 --> 03:47.059
BRIAN'S ALL--
HIS EARS CLOSE DOWN.

03:47.093 --> 03:48.227
"NO, NO, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT."

03:48.261 --> 03:50.429
WHATEVER.
GROW UP.

03:50.463 --> 03:52.198
THIS ISN'T NURSERY SCHOOL.

03:52.231 --> 03:53.466
I DON'T REALLY GIVE A
ABOUT THEIR FEELINGS.

03:53.499 --> 03:54.634
IT WOULD BE GREAT

03:54.667 --> 03:56.202
TO HAVE SOMEBODY
OF CHEF RAMSAY'S CALIBER

03:56.235 --> 03:57.603
COME IN AND SHOW BRIAN
THAT HE'S NOT RIGHT.

03:59.038 --> 04:00.000
I DON'T NEED HELP COOKING.

04:00.000 --> 04:01.874
I DON'T NEED HELP COOKING.

04:01.908 --> 04:03.576
BEFORE, I WOULD JUST
LEAVE THE KITCHEN

04:03.609 --> 04:05.144
AND LET HIM GO
ON HIS WAY,

04:05.177 --> 04:08.481
BUT THE BUSINESS,
IT'S FLOUNDERING.

04:08.514 --> 04:10.016
THERE'S NO WAY
OF ANYBODY KNOWING

04:10.049 --> 04:11.517
THAT IT WAS A RESTAURANT.

04:11.550 --> 04:13.119
YOU KNOW, WE PUT SIGNS
ON THE WINDOWS

04:13.152 --> 04:15.221
AND THINGS OF THAT NATURE,

04:15.254 --> 04:16.956
BUT WE STILL HAVEN'T GOTTEN
A SIGN OUT FRONT.

04:16.989 --> 04:19.058
WE JUST DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY.

04:19.091 --> 04:21.661
BUDDY IS IN DEBT SOMEWHERE IN
THE HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS.

04:21.694 --> 04:23.729
MY FATHER'S INVESTED

04:23.763 --> 04:25.831
EVERYTHING HE HAS
INTO THIS BUSINESS.

04:25.865 --> 04:28.634
HIS WHOLE LIFE AS A COP
AND RETIREMENT

04:28.668 --> 04:29.969
AND PENSION
AND THIS AND THAT,

04:30.002 --> 04:31.270
IT'S GONE.

04:31.304 --> 04:33.205
I ABSOLUTELY WORRY
ABOUT BUDDY'S HEALTH.

04:35.875 --> 04:38.110
I WORRY A LOT
ABOUT HIS HEALTH.

04:38.144 --> 04:40.079
IT'S NOT MY BOAT AND I
DON'T WANNA GO DOWN WITH IT.

04:40.112 --> 04:41.614
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY HE THINKS

04:41.647 --> 04:43.149
HE CAN BE
THE WAY HE IS.

04:43.182 --> 04:44.483
IF IT DOESN'T WORK,

04:44.517 --> 04:47.586
IT SCARES ME TO THINK
HOW MUCH

04:47.620 --> 04:49.488
NOT ONLY DOES HE LOSE,
HOW MUCH EVERYBODY LOSES,

04:49.522 --> 04:52.024
'CAUSE WE NEED THIS
FOR OUR FAMILY.

04:52.058 --> 04:54.126
I'M WORRYING
EVERY NIGHT GOING TO BED,

04:54.160 --> 04:56.629
"ARE YOU GONNA BE ABLE
TO PAY THIS MORTGAGE?"

04:56.662 --> 04:59.865
AND TRY TO JUST BARELY
SCRAPE BY AND MAKE IT HAPPEN.

04:59.899 --> 05:00.000
I CAN'T DESCRIBE TO YOU
HOW STRESSFUL THAT IS.

05:00.000 --> 05:04.337
I CAN'T DESCRIBE TO YOU
HOW STRESSFUL THAT IS.

05:04.370 --> 05:07.006
I CAN'T.

05:18.217 --> 05:19.685
HERE I'M AT FINN McCOOL'S

05:19.719 --> 05:21.087
TO HELP A FAMILY
THAT ARE IN CRISIS,

05:21.120 --> 05:22.621
AND BLOODY HELL,

05:22.655 --> 05:24.924
IT LOOKS LIKE A FUNERAL PARLOR
FROM THE OUTSIDE.

05:24.957 --> 05:26.292
NOT A RESTAURANT.

05:26.325 --> 05:27.593
GOD.

05:27.626 --> 05:30.000
IT'S SO GRIM.

05:30.000 --> 05:31.464
IT'S SO GRIM.

05:31.497 --> 05:33.132
HELLO.

05:33.165 --> 05:34.533
HI.
HOW ARE YOU?

05:34.567 --> 05:36.402
BUDDY MAZIO.
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

05:36.435 --> 05:38.437
MY FIRST IMPRESSIONS
OF CHEF RAMSAY

05:38.471 --> 05:40.873
WERE THAT HE'S
AN INTENSE MAN.

05:40.906 --> 05:42.808
I DIDN'T KNOW
IF HE WAS GONNA BE

05:42.842 --> 05:44.777
SOME KIND OF A BASTARD
OR AN EGO MAN

05:44.810 --> 05:45.978
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

05:46.012 --> 05:47.413
THIS IS MY SON JASON.

05:47.446 --> 05:48.781
JASON, NICE TO SEE YOU.

05:48.814 --> 05:50.049
NICE TO MEET YOU.
GOOD.
HELLO.

05:50.082 --> 05:51.083
THIS IS CAROL.

05:51.117 --> 05:52.385
CAROL, NICE TO SEE YOU.

05:52.418 --> 05:53.619
MY FIRST IMPRESSION OF GORDON,

05:53.652 --> 05:55.054
I THINK HE'S ADORABLE.

05:55.087 --> 05:57.923
I WOULD LOVE
TO GET MY HANDS ON GORDON.

05:57.957 --> 05:59.625
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER-IN-LAW
MELISSA.

05:59.658 --> 06:00.000
MELISSA, HELLO.

06:00.000 --> 06:01.093
MELISSA, HELLO.

06:01.127 --> 06:02.661
MY SON BRIAN.

06:02.695 --> 06:04.563
CHEF, HOW ARE YOU?
ARE YOU WELL?

06:04.597 --> 06:06.632
THE FIRST TIME I SAW HIM
WHEN HE CAME IN,

06:06.665 --> 06:08.801
I WAS DEFINITELY
A LITTLE SKEPTICAL.

06:08.834 --> 06:11.070
I DO MY OWN THING BACK HERE,
I'M VERY CONTENT WITH THAT.

06:11.103 --> 06:13.139
SO LET'S START WITH CAROL.

06:13.172 --> 06:15.207
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

06:15.241 --> 06:18.310
WE HAVE PROBLEMS
WITH STAFF.

06:18.344 --> 06:20.079
UH-HUH.
WE HAVE PROBLEMS
WITH BRIAN.

06:20.112 --> 06:22.114
UH, OKAY.

06:22.148 --> 06:24.817
HE'S, UH,
A BIT ARROGANT AND--

06:24.850 --> 06:26.352
A LOT ARROGANT.

06:26.385 --> 06:28.721
BECAUSE I SAY
WHAT NEEDS TO BE SAID

06:28.754 --> 06:30.000
AND YOU PEOPLE DON'T WANT
TO HEAR IT, TOO BAD.

06:30.000 --> 06:30.489
AND YOU PEOPLE DON'T WANT
TO HEAR IT, TOO BAD.

06:32.124 --> 06:34.260
WE'RE HERE
TO MAKEMONEY.
YEAH.

06:34.293 --> 06:36.162
AND IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DO YOUR JOB, GET OUT.

06:36.195 --> 06:37.963
I'M SORRY, BRIAN,
BUT IT DOES STEM--

06:37.997 --> 06:39.365
IT STEMS FROM HIM,

06:39.398 --> 06:42.535
BECAUSE HE WON'T LISTEN
TO BUDDY.

06:42.568 --> 06:43.636
AN EXAMPLE LIKE?

06:43.669 --> 06:45.071
VALENTINE'S DAY.

06:45.104 --> 06:47.206
I WANTED HIM TO DO
A NICE VALENTINE'S DAY MENU.

06:47.239 --> 06:48.808
HE DIDN'T SEE THE NEED FOR IT
'CAUSE WE'RE AN IRISH PUB.

06:48.841 --> 06:49.775
HE DIDN'T THINK ANYBODY
WOULD COME IN

06:49.809 --> 06:52.578
FOR AN IRISH PUB
FOR VALENTINES DAY.

06:52.611 --> 06:54.647
IT'S THE NIGHT BEFORE
VALENTINES DAY AND YOU SAY,

06:54.680 --> 06:55.347
"WE WANT TO DO
A VALENTINES MENU TOMORROW."

06:58.684 --> 07:00.000
TALKING ABOUT
TWO WEEKS BEFORE.

07:00.000 --> 07:00.419
TALKING ABOUT
TWO WEEKS BEFORE.

07:00.453 --> 07:02.088
TALKING ABOUT
A WEEK BEFORE.

07:02.121 --> 07:04.123
NO, NO, NO, NO.
IT'S TOO LATE FOR ME TO ORDER.

07:04.156 --> 07:05.991
BUT IT'S
YOUR RESPONSIBILITY

07:06.025 --> 07:07.159
TO HAVE COME UP WITH IT
WEEKS BEFORE

07:07.193 --> 07:08.627
'CAUSE YOU ARE
THE HEAD CHEF.

07:08.661 --> 07:10.496
WE DON'T ADVERTISE.

07:10.529 --> 07:11.464
SCREW 'EM.

07:11.497 --> 07:12.665
OH, BOY.

07:12.698 --> 07:14.366
RIGHT NOW,
I'M HUNGRY.

07:14.400 --> 07:15.868
I WANT TO TASTE THE FOOD.

07:15.901 --> 07:17.570
AND LET'S MEET AFTER,
SHALL WE?

07:17.603 --> 07:19.071
I WAS PRETTY NERVOUS.

07:19.105 --> 07:21.107
I WONDER WHAT
HE'S GONNA SEE.

07:21.140 --> 07:22.608
I WONDER IF WE'RE GONNA GET
REALLY BLASTED.

07:22.641 --> 07:23.909
YOU KNOW?

07:23.943 --> 07:25.845
THERE'S OUR
LUNCH MENU.
THANK YOU.

07:25.878 --> 07:27.379
I'M LIKE, "I'M ABOUT
TO SERVE CHEF RAMSAY.

07:27.413 --> 07:29.281
LIKE, THIS IS SO COOL."

