UM, HONESTLY, IT'S FROZEN.

07:34.086 --> 07:36.589
HMM.

07:36.622 --> 07:39.658
I'LL START
WITH THE, UH,

07:39.692 --> 07:41.927
FINN'S SPRING ROLL, PLEASE.

07:41.961 --> 07:43.629
GOOD CHOICE.
THANK YOU.

07:43.662 --> 07:45.531
CAN I GO FOR THE SALMON
AS WELL, PLEASE?

07:45.564 --> 07:47.099
AND FOR THE MAIN COURSE, I'LL
HAVE A SHEPHERD'S PIE,

07:47.133 --> 07:48.100
PLEASE, I THINK.

07:48.134 --> 07:49.168
OKAY.
THANK YOU, MELISSA.

07:49.201 --> 07:50.236
YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:04.950 --> 08:06.585
I'M A VERY CONFIDENT PERSON.

08:06.619 --> 08:08.521
AND I'VE BEEN IN THE KITCHEN
FOR A LONG TIME.

08:08.554 --> 08:12.057
I'M ALMOST POSITIVE
WE'LL GET A GOOD REVIEW.

08:12.091 --> 08:14.793
WHEN YOU GET
A FAMILY BUSINESS RIGHT,

08:14.827 --> 08:16.695
IT GOES ON FOR GENERATIONS.

08:16.729 --> 08:18.631
AND HERE,

08:18.664 --> 08:21.800
IT DOESN'T FEEL LIKE
A FAMILY-RUN BUSINESS AT ALL.

08:21.834 --> 08:24.403
PUBS ARE FULL OF ATMOSPHERE,
FUN.

08:24.436 --> 08:26.005
IT'S GOT TWEED KNIT CURTAINS,

08:26.038 --> 08:27.273
LIKE YOU'RE GOING TO VISIT
YOUR GRANNY.

08:27.306 --> 08:29.642
WEIRD.

08:29.675 --> 08:30.000
HERE YOU ARE,
SOME SPRING ROLLS

08:30.000 --> 08:31.177
HERE YOU ARE,
SOME SPRING ROLLS

08:31.210 --> 08:32.811
WITH COLMAN'S
MUSTARD.

08:32.845 --> 08:33.812
WOW.

08:33.846 --> 08:35.648
GOD.

08:38.217 --> 08:41.787
IT'S A VERY STRANGE,
BIZARRE LOOKING SPRING ROLL.

08:44.623 --> 08:46.559
DAMN.

08:46.592 --> 08:48.127
ARE THEY POPULAR
ON THE MENU?

08:48.160 --> 08:50.496
UM, PEOPLE
REALLY LIKE THEM.

08:50.529 --> 08:53.098
NO DOUBT HALF THE CUSTOMERS
ARE DRUNK.

08:58.037 --> 08:59.405
NOT A BIG HIT.

08:59.438 --> 09:00.000
HE DIDN'T LIKE IT?
NO.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.106
HE DIDN'T LIKE IT?
NO.

09:01.140 --> 09:02.942
BRIAN'S IN THE KITCHEN,
LIKE, WONDERING.

09:02.975 --> 09:04.510
I'M JUST LIKE, "NOPE."

09:06.412 --> 09:08.247
HE REALLY THOUGHT THAT
I WAS GONNA WALK BACK THERE

09:08.280 --> 09:09.915
AND BE LIKE,
"HE LOVED IT."

09:09.949 --> 09:11.650
YOU KNOW, "HE WANTS YOU
TO COME WORK FOR HIM."

09:11.684 --> 09:14.186
COME ON.

09:15.854 --> 09:18.357
LET ME GET YOU
SOME CLEAN SILVERWARE.

09:18.390 --> 09:19.792
THANK YOU.
GOD.

09:19.825 --> 09:21.594
AND WHAT'S THIS STUFF HERE,
PLEASE, MELISSA?

09:21.627 --> 09:23.429
ON TOP
IS A BALSAMIC REDUCTION.

09:23.462 --> 09:24.763
HE LIKES TO USE THAT
A LOT.

09:24.797 --> 09:25.598
HE LIKES THAT,
DOESN'T HE?

09:25.631 --> 09:26.899
YES, HE DOES.

09:26.932 --> 09:28.834
ON EVERYTHING,
HE PUTS A LITTLE DRIZZLE ON.

09:28.867 --> 09:30.000
A LITTLE?

09:30.000 --> 09:31.070
A LITTLE?

09:31.103 --> 09:32.938
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

09:32.972 --> 09:35.040
ALWAYS THE SIGN
OF A VERY INSECURE CHEF

09:35.074 --> 09:37.710
WHEN HE MACERATES EVERYTHING
IN BALSAMIC VINEGAR.

09:37.743 --> 09:40.546
LOOK AT THIS.

09:41.580 --> 09:42.982
HORRIBLE.

09:43.015 --> 09:45.184
DOESN'T TASTE LIKE SALMON
AT ALL.

